      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations via benchmark problems at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Solver verification confirmed against ASME V&V 20 benchmark lid-driven cavity and pipe-flow cases. Order-of-accuracy tests confirm second-order spatial convergence consistent with solver documentation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be reported for primary QoI (shear stress and velocity magnitude) with GCI < 5% on the fine grid.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the FDA pump geometry. GCI for area-averaged wall shear stress is 3.1% and for volume-averaged scalar stress is 2.8% on the fine mesh (8.4 M cells). Richardson extrapolation applied; asymptotic range confirmed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity) must be reproduced in simulation within stated measurement uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow rate (3.5 L/min ± 2%), impeller speed (2500 RPM ± 0.5%), and fluid temperature (37 °C ± 0.5 °C) are matched to PIV test conditions. Fluid properties use water-glycerol mixture matching blood viscosity at 37 °C."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., RMSE or validation uncertainty) must be computed for velocity fields at all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Velocity magnitude RMSE against PIV data is 0.07 m/s (< 8% of peak velocity) across all five flow-speed combinations. Validation uncertainty computed per ASME V&V 20; model error falls within experimental uncertainty bands at four of five operating points."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (velocity, shear stress) must be demonstrably linked to the hemolysis prediction QoI (relative hemolysis index RH).",
      "rationale": "The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) is driven directly by scalar stress magnitude derived from the validated velocity field. Sensitivity analysis confirms RH varies monotonically with scalar stress, establishing the linkage between validated and decision QoIs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must be conducted on the same or geometrically similar pump at operating conditions spanning the COU envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation uses the FDA benchmark centrifugal pump geometry under identical operating conditions as the COU (3.5–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Geometric similarity is exact; fluid analogue (water-glycerol) is accepted per FDA guidance for hemolysis CFD studies."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated with residuals below 1e-5 for all transport equations and monitored QoI variation below 0.1% over final 200 iterations.",
      "rationale": "All continuity, momentum, and turbulence equation residuals reach 1e-6. Monitored outlet pressure and volume-averaged scalar stress show variation below 0.05% over the final 500 iterations, confirming iterative convergence."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup must be reviewed by an independent analyst and documented in a simulation plan prior to execution.",
      "rationale": "A simulation plan was prepared and reviewed by a second qualified CFD analyst prior to case execution. Boundary condition inputs, turbulence model selection, and post-processing scripts were independently verified. No discrepancies were identified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive model selection must be justified against available literature and sensitivity analysis for the pump flow regime.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on prior FDA interlaboratory study findings and internal sensitivity comparison against realizable k-epsilon. Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model validated against published erythrocyte fragility data. Sensitivity of RH to model-form choice quantified at ±12%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Uncertainty in material properties (blood viscosity, red blood cell mechanical properties) and geometric tolerances must be propagated through the model to bound QoI uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Propagation of input uncertainty for blood rheological parameters and manufactured geometric tolerances was considered beyond the scope of the current analysis phase. A deterministic nominal-condition simulation was performed instead. This factor is deferred to a subsequent uncertainty quantification study planned for the design verification phase."
    },
