      "acceptanceCriteria": "A formal equivalency argument must demonstrate that water-glycerol analogue fluid parameters are sufficiently representative of in-vivo blood properties for hemolysis prediction purposes.",
      "rationale": "Formal equivalency documentation mapping water-glycerol analogue properties to patient blood properties across the haematocrit range was considered beyond the scope of this assessment. The analogue fluid choice follows FDA guidance precedent but a quantitative bridging analysis was not conducted within this package."
